  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity exercise was conducted informally during model development to examine the influence of viscosity and inlet boundary condition variation on the relative hemolysis index; those results were reviewed by the assessment team and found to support model adequacy at MRL 2. No structured uncertainty quantification campaign was scoped for this assessment level, and the screening results are summarized in the factor rationales below rather than as a separate formal analysis artifact.",
